a/Set/Defs.html#Set.univ\">Set.univ</a>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ContDiff/Defs.html#ContDiffOn\">ContDiffOn</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">(↑<span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">q</span> : <span class=\"fn\">P</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Convolution.html#MeasureTheory.convolution\">convolution</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">q</span>.1</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">L</span> <span class=\"fn\">μ</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">q</span>.2</span></span>)</span> (<span class=\"fn\">s</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/SProd.html#SProd.sprod\">×ˢ</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set.univ\">Set.univ</a>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The convolution `f * g` is `C^n` when `f` is locally integrable and `g` is `C^n` and compactly\nsupported. Version where `g` depends on an additional parameter in an open subset `s` of a\nparameter space `P` (and the compact support `k` is independent of the parameter in `s`). ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ContDiff/Convolution.html#MeasureTheory.contDiffOn_convolution_right_with_param","kind":"theorem","line":338,"name":"MeasureTheory.contDiffOn_convolution_right_with_param","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ContDiff/Convolution.lean#L338-L394"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ContDiff/Convolution.html#MeasureTheory.contDiffOn_convolution_right_with_param_aux\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span